    "text": "article_14111689-8c21-4e67-a8ce-af01bf169e38 agent agent high 2026-07-05T03:45:02.067Z 2026-07-05T03:45:02.067Z article Project overview Project-Overview Wikiwiki keeps local article-first project wikis beside the code, with structured records as the durable source of truth. Wikiwiki is a local-first project wiki system for code repos. It stores durable knowledge as structured JSONL records, renders article-led Markdown into `wiki/`, and builds a static `wiki-site/` that agents and humans can both inspect.\n\nUse it when a repo needs living documentation that stays beside the code rather than in a hosted service or hidden memory layer. Articles are the public wiki pages; concepts, decisions, notes, events, symbols, and links are the evidence ledger behind them.\n\nThe CLI stays scriptable and provider-agnostic. Agentic IDEs can use the same deterministic commands to inspect status, capture records, regenerate docs, and close out work without turning the wiki into an opaque AI artifact. product overview homepage overview what is wikiwiki README.md docs/concepts.md src/core/store.ts src/core/renderer.ts src/core/site.ts audience:all product overview homepage"
