    "text": "article_1e1ed20d-081b-4fa0-9cf5-3a6c06331325 agent agent high 2026-07-05T03:45:02.167Z 2026-07-05T03:45:02.167Z article Getting started Getting-Started Install the npm package, set up a repo wiki, generate the site, and verify the first local output. Install Wikiwiki in the repo that should own the wiki, then run setup from that repo root:\n\n`test \"$(npm prefix)\" = \"$PWD\" || npm init -y`\n\n`npm install --prefix \"$PWD\" --save-dev @thjodann/wk`\n\n`npx wk setup --profile mixed --audience all`\n\nAfter setup, generate the human-facing output with `wk validate`, `wk render`, and `wk site --audience all`. If the repo wants a branded static site, run `wk theme preview --json` first, then `wk theme init` once the preview looks right.\n\nThe first successful verification is simple: open `wiki-site/index.html` and confirm the generated site loads, search works, and source/wiki links resolve. getting-started instructions homepage quick start first install README.md docs/setup.md docs/reference.md audience:user getting-started instructions homepage"
