    "text": "article_d2716fa1-9e38-45c4-a428-4e14b8ee399e agent agent high 2026-07-05T03:45:02.268Z 2026-07-05T03:45:02.268Z article Agent setup Agent-Setup Install the Codex-compatible wk skill so agents can run the same local wiki protocol as the CLI. For Codex-compatible IDEs, run `wk setup --profile mixed --audience all --agent codex` when initializing a repo. To refresh only the companion skill later, run `wk install-agent codex` or `wk install-agent codex --yes` after previewing the destination.\n\nThe installed `/wk` skill gives agents the repo protocol for `status`, `spin`, records, render/site, closeout, and Beads coordination. It treats structured records as the source of truth and keeps generated Markdown and static-site files deterministic.\n\nA bare `wk`, `/wk`, `$wk`, or linked `$wk` invocation is intentionally lightweight: if `wiki-site/index.html` exists, the agent should return one concise local link to that generated site instead of running status/spin, starting a server, explaining the skill, or modifying files.\n\nFor CLI updates, install `@thjodann/wk@latest` through npm or the repo package manager, then rerun `./node_modules/.bin/wk install-agent codex --yes` to refresh the installed skill from the packaged source. agent setup instructions codex setup wk skill skills/wk/SKILL.md skills/wk/agents/openai.yaml docs/setup.md src/cli/commands/installAgent.ts src/cli/commands/setup.ts audience:all agent codex instructions"
