    "text": "article_d44352a8-8230-403f-9176-12d6d1a648c2 agent agent high 2026-07-05T03:45:02.368Z 2026-07-05T03:45:02.368Z article Workflows Workflows Use status/spin for orientation, records for durable knowledge, render/site for output, and closeout for reviewable end-of-work packets. A normal Wikiwiki loop starts with `wk status --json` and `wk spin --profile mixed --json`. `status` reports the store, generated outputs, git changes, and integration state; `spin` turns current repo context into a deterministic first-pass wiki recipe.\n\nCapture durable public knowledge as article records. Use concepts, decisions, notes, events, symbols, and links as supporting evidence, maintainer context, and source anchors. Prefer CLI record commands over editing `.wikiwiki/records/*.jsonl` by hand.\n\nWhen records or human-facing wiki output changes, run `wk validate`, `wk render`, and `wk site --audience all`. Generated files in `wiki/` and `wiki-site/` should be regenerated from records, not manually edited.\n\nAfter meaningful work, run `wk closeout --profile mixed --audience all --json`, review the closeout packet under `.wikiwiki/drafts/closeout/`, and apply only drafts that are true, useful, and properly sourced. workflows maintenance instructions daily workflow agent workflow docs/workflows.md docs/reference.md skills/wk/SKILL.md src/cli/commands/status.ts src/cli/commands/spin.ts src/cli/commands/closeout.ts audience:all workflow instructions maintenance"
