    "text": "article_0813c454-1df9-4ec4-b19a-dde8223e03f8 agent agent high 2026-07-05T03:45:02.467Z 2026-07-05T03:45:02.467Z article FAQ and troubleshooting FAQ-Troubleshooting Common fixes for npm installs, missing generated sites, Beads coordination, and npm Trusted Publishing releases. If npm installs Wikiwiki in the wrong place, check `npm prefix`. In non-JavaScript repos, create a local `package.json` first or use `npm install --prefix \"$PWD\" --save-dev @thjodann/wk` so npm does not climb to an ancestor project.\n\nIf the generated site is missing, run `wk site --audience all` or the repo's `wiki:site` script when present. A bare `/wk` invocation should show an existing generated site, but it should not start a server or generate a site on its own.\n\nIf a repo uses Beads, Wikiwiki detects `.beads/` and can include read-only task context when explicitly enabled. Beads remains the task system; Wikiwiki records only durable project knowledge and public wiki content.\n\nIf npm Trusted Publishing rejects a release, publish manually with the package owner account and npm 2FA, then let the GitHub Release workflow rerun or skip the already-published version. npm versions are immutable, so every release needs a fresh package version. faq troubleshooting release faq troubleshooting README.md docs/setup.md docs/reference.md .github/workflows/publish-npm.yml audience:user faq troubleshooting release"
